        "text": "POST\n/v1/inboxes\nCreate inbox\n---------------------------------------------\nCreate an Inbox\nThis endpoint allows you to create a new inbox with basic configurations.\n\nRequest Body:\nemail: The email address you want to create the inbox for. (e.g., test@gmail.com)\npassword: The password for the inbox. (e.g., xyzqwert123)\nsender_first: First name of the sender. (e.g., Samuel)\nsender_last: Last name of the sender. (e.g., Jackson)\nplan: Type of subscription plan for the inbox. Options include: basic, pro, max, send_only, monitoring.\nfrequency: Defines the email warm-up process, with properties like starting_baseline, increase_per_day, max_sends_per_day, reply_rate.\ntimezone (optional, Pro/Max only): The IANA timezone identifier for the inbox. (e.g., America/New_York, Europe/London, Asia/Tokyo). If not specified, defaults to Etc/UTC. Requires Pro or Max plan.\nAuto-Configuration of SMTP and IMAP:\nWhen you provide an email and password, the system automatically configures the SMTP and IMAP settings based on the MX record of the email domain.\nThis auto-configuration is suitable for most users and simplifies the setup process.\nAdvanced Configuration:\nIf you need to specify different passwords for SMTP and IMAP, or if you want to configure SMTP and IMAP settings directly, use the advanced creation endpoint: /inboxes/advanced (POST).\nThe advanced endpoint allows for more granular control over the SMTP and IMAP configurations.\nNotes:\nInbox Type: Only smtp_imap inboxes are supported. OAuth inboxes are not supported via this API.\nEnsure all required fields are provided to avoid a Bad Request error.\nHandle error responses appropriately, including 401 Unauthorized, 403 Forbidden (e.g., a free user trying to create a pro inbox), or 409 Conflict (e.g., inbox already in use).\nParameters\nTry it out\nNo parameters\n\nRequest body\n\napplication/json\nExample Value\nSchema\n{\n  \"email\": \"test@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"xyzqwert123\",\n  \"sender_first\": \"Samuel\",\n  \"sender_last\": \"Jackson\",\n  \"plan\": \"basic\",\n  \"frequency\": {\n    \"starting_baseline\": 0,\n    \"increase_per_day\": 2,\n    \"max_sends_per_day\": 75,\n    \"reply_rate\": 30\n  },\n  \"timezone\": \"America/New_York\"\n}\nResponses\nCode\tDescription\tLinks\n201\t\nSuccessfully created inbox.\n\nMedia type\n\napplication/json\nControls Accept header.\nExample Value\nSchema\n{\n  \"code\": \"created\",\n  \"inbox_id\": \"inbox_gnl2ZEFDY850oJ4o\",\n  \"details\": \"The inbox was successfully created.\",\n  \"isThisFirstOne\": true\n}\nNo links\n400\t\nBad Request\n\nMedia type\n\napplication/json\nExample Value\nSchema\n{\n  \"statusCode\": 400,\n  \"message\": \"smtp_imap inboxes must have the smtp object.\",\n  \"error\": \"Bad Request\"\n}\nNo links\n401\t\nError: Unauthorized\n\nMedia type\n\napplication/json\nExample Value\nSchema\n{\n  \"statusCode\": 401,\n  \"message\": \"Invalid api key\",\n  \"error\": \"Unauthorized\"\n}\nNo links\n403\t\nForbidden\n\nMedia type\n\napplication/json\nExample Value\nSchema\n{\n  \"statusCode\": 403,\n  \"message\": \"Free user is not allowed to create a max inbox\",\n  \"error\": \"Forbidden\"\n}\nNo links\n409\t\nConflict\n\nMedia type\n\napplication/json\nExample Value\nSchema\n{\n  \"statusCode\": 409,\n  \"message\": \"Inbox is already in use\",\n  \"error\": \"Conflict\"\n}\nNo links\n429\t\nError: Too Many Requests\n\nMedia type\n\napplication/json\nExample Value\nSchema\n{\n  \"statusCode\": 429,\n  \"message\": \"Too Many Requests\",\n  \"error\": \"Too Many Requests\"\n}\nNo links\n\nGET\n/v1/inboxes/{id}\nGet inbox details\n-------------------------------------------------------------\nGet Inbox Details\nThis endpoint allows you to retrieve detailed information for a specific inbox.\n\nInbox Details:\ninbox_id: The unique ID of the inbox. (e.g., inbox_GM5i7HCSJ9bMN10O)\nstatus: Current status of the inbox. (e.g., paused)\ntype: Type of the inbox. (e.g., smtp_imap)\nemail: Email address linked with the inbox. (e.g., example@example.com)\nfilter_id: (DEPRECATED - no longer used, see identifier instead) Previously appeared in email subjects. Maintained for backward compatibility only.\nidentifier: The unique 8-digit identifier that appears in the email body as a phone-like number. Use this to filter emails from our network. (e.g., 12345678)\nscore: Landing score of the inbox indicating its health. (e.g., 98)\ncreated_at: Timestamp of when the inbox was created. (e.g., 1646248718)\nfrequency: Object detailing the email warm-up process.\nstarting_baseline: Initial number of emails sent on day one. (e.g., 20)\nincrease_per_day: Daily increment of sent emails. (e.g., 4)\nmax_sends_per_day: Maximum emails that can be sent daily. (e.g., 50)\nreply_rate: Desired percentage of received replies. (e.g., 50)\nlast_sends_per_day: Number of emails sent the previous day. (e.g., 24)\nstrategy: Strategy used for the warm-up process. (e.g., progressive)\nreputation: Object detailing the reputation scores.\nscore: Overall reputation score. (e.g., 98)\nscore_google: Reputation score for Google. (e.g., 100)\nscore_microsoft: Reputation score for Microsoft. (e.g., 95)\nscore_all_other: Reputation score for other providers. (e.g., 97)\nplan: Type of subscription plan for the inbox. This can be one of the following: basic, pro, max, send_only, monitoring.\nemail_topics: We use artificial intelligence to generate message content that is unrecognisable from what a human would write. This array contains the topics that are used to generate the content. (e.g., [\"Affiliate Offers\", \"Real Estate\"])\nschedule: Object detailing the sending schedule for each day of the week. Each day has a start and end time in hours. (e.g., Monday's schedule: 9:00 to 17:00)\ntimezone: The timezone set for the inbox. (e.g., Etc/UTC)\nlanguage: The language of warmup emails set for the inbox. (e.g., english). This can be one of the following: english, german, french, spanish, polish, italian, dutch, danish, finnish, portuguese, slovak, russian, swedish, norwegian, turkish, indonesian, ukrainian, romanian, czech, hungarian, malay, bulgarian, serbian.\nesp_priority: The priority of the inbox for different email service providers. This object has the following properties:\ngoogle: Is Google ESP in priority. (e.g., true)\noutlook: Is Outlook ESP in priority. (e.g., false)\nall_other: Are all other ESPs in priority. (e.g., false)\nextended_reply: Determines if warm-up email replies should include previous message history (e.g., true). When enabled, replies mimic natural email conversation patterns by including the original message content.\nhealth_check: Object containing inbox health check information with scores and timestamps.\nmx: MX records configuration with score (0-1), last check timestamp, and array of MX records.\nspf: SPF record configuration with score (0-1), last check timestamp, and record value.\ndmarc: DMARC record configuration with score (0-1), last check timestamp, and record value.\ndomain_blacklists: Blacklist check results with score (0-1), last check timestamp, and array of blacklist results.\nwarmup_days: Warmup progress with score (0-1), last check timestamp, and number of warmup days.\nNotes:\nAlways ensure you're querying the right inbox by its inbox_id.\nThe response provides a comprehensive overview of the inbox, including its frequency, reputation, schedule, and more.\nHealth check scores range from 0 to 1, where 1 indicates optimal configuration.\nlast_check_at timestamps are in ISO 8601 format and indicate when each check was last performed.\nParameters\nTry it out\nName\tDescription\nid *\nstring\n(path)\nID of the inbox\n\nExample : inbox_GM5i7HCSJ9bMN10O\n\ninbox_PA4kMVkvl\nResponses\nCurl\n\ncurl -X 'GET' \\\n  'https://api.warmupinbox.com/v1/inboxes/inbox_PA4kMVkvl' \\\n  -H 'accept: application/json' \\\n  -H 'x-api-key: ac78f6953b9486ff2eacecab7d9ff7d7ccdd3edcb88b0c7c73c4fd56f0b42744'\nRequest URL\nhttp